---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About zenprocess.ai — Enterprise IT for Building Materials Distribution"
  description="20+ years enterprise IT and CTO experience, now focused on building materials distributors. Houston, TX."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#000510]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold mb-6">
        Built by someone who's done this before.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-[#f5f4f0]/80 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        zenprocess.ai brings 20+ years of enterprise architecture and CTO experience to building materials distribution — the industry where we saw the biggest gap between the data companies have and the insights they can actually use.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Vinh's Story -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#000510]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-12 items-start">
        <!-- Vinh's Photo -->
        <img
          src="/vinh-photo.jpg"
          alt="Vinh Truong — Co-Founder & AI Architect of zenprocess.ai"
          class="w-64 h-64 object-cover rounded-xl border border-white/10 shrink-0"
        />

        <!-- Content -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Vinh Truong — Co-Founder & AI Architect</h2>

          <div class="space-y-6 text-[#f5f4f0]/80 leading-relaxed text-lg">
            <p>
              I spent 20+ years leading enterprise IT at the VP and CTO level — building architecture, modernizing systems, and delivering technology programs worth $80M+ in regulated, complex environments.
            </p>
            <p>
              When I started working with building materials distributors, I saw something familiar: smart operators running solid businesses on good ERPs, but drowning in Excel because they couldn't get their data out in a useful form. The purchasing team tracks 800+ inventory exceptions in a spreadsheet. The finance team rebuilds the same report every Friday. Nobody has real-time visibility across warehouses.
            </p>
            <p>
              I've solved this problem before — just in different industries. The tools are proven. The architecture is well-understood. The gap is that nobody has packaged it for this vertical.
            </p>
            <p>
              That's what zenprocess.ai does. We take enterprise-grade data architecture — the kind you'd find at a Fortune 500 — and apply it to mid-market building materials companies. Same rigor. Same security. Fraction of the cost and timeline.
            </p>
            <p>
              I don't subcontract. I architect, and my team and I build your system directly. When you work with zenprocess, you're working with me.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Building Materials -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#000510]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Why this industry</h2>
      <p class="text-[#f5f4f0]/80 text-lg mb-8">
        We chose this vertical because the problems are urgent, measurable, and solvable.
      </p>

      <ul class="space-y-4 text-[#f5f4f0]/80 text-lg mb-10">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-2 w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-[#16A34A] shrink-0"></span>
          <span><strong class="text-white">ERP data is locked</strong> — SAP, NetSuite, or Sage runs the transactions, but nobody can get reporting without Excel</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-2 w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-[#16A34A] shrink-0"></span>
          <span><strong class="text-white">Manual processes scale poorly</strong> — what worked at 500 SKUs breaks at 3,000+</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-2 w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-[#16A34A] shrink-0"></span>
          <span><strong class="text-white">Multi-warehouse complexity</strong> — inventory spread across 3-14 regional DCs with no unified view</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-2 w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-[#16A34A] shrink-0"></span>
          <span><strong class="text-white">Overseas supply chain risk</strong> — 90-120 day lead times demand proactive systems, not reactive spreadsheets</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-2 w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-[#16A34A] shrink-0"></span>
          <span><strong class="text-white">Industry consolidation</strong> — PE acquisitions are creating integration pressure across newly combined operations</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[#f5f4f0]/80 text-lg">
        We've already built and validated a solution for a national building materials distributor — multi-warehouse, SAP, 3,000+ SKUs. The architecture works. Now we're applying it to more companies in the same space.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Credentials -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#000510]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-xl border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-6">
          <p class="text-sm text-[#16A34A] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Experience</p>
          <p class="text-white text-lg font-medium">20+ years enterprise IT & CTO leadership</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-xl border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-6">
          <p class="text-sm text-[#16A34A] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Scale</p>
          <p class="text-white text-lg font-medium">$80M+ in technology initiatives delivered</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-xl border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-6">
          <p class="text-sm text-[#16A34A] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Architecture</p>
          <p class="text-white text-lg font-medium">SAP, cloud data warehouses, ETL/ELT, custom dashboards</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-xl border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-6">
          <p class="text-sm text-[#16A34A] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Security</p>
          <p class="text-white text-lg font-medium">CISSP-aligned practices, HIPAA/SOX/PCI-DSS background</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-xl border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-6">
          <p class="text-sm text-[#16A34A] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Location</p>
          <p class="text-white text-lg font-medium">Houston, TX</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-xl border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-6">
          <p class="text-sm text-[#16A34A] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Focus</p>
          <p class="text-white text-lg font-medium">Building materials distribution — exclusively</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#000510]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Want to talk?</h2>
      <p class="text-[#f5f4f0]/80 text-lg mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        I'm happy to spend 30 minutes understanding your operation. No sales pitch.
      </p>
      <a
        href="https://links.zenprocess.ai/widget/booking/rcoKJifJJA46bRI9fTEr"
        target="_blank"
        class="inline-block bg-[#16A34A] hover:bg-[#15803D] text-white font-semibold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg transition-colors text-lg shadow-[0_4px_20px_rgba(22,163,74,0.3)]"
      >
        Book a Discovery Call
      </a>
      <p class="text-[#978aa1] mt-6">
        Or email <a href="mailto:info@zenprocess.ai" class="text-[#22C55E] hover:text-[#16A34A]">info@zenprocess.ai</a> | <a href="tel:+18329742818" class="text-[#22C55E] hover:text-[#16A34A]">(832) 974-2818</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
